---
alwaysApply: true
---

- The /docs folder must exist and contain these files:
    docs/architecture.md
    docs/data_pipeline.md
    docs/optimization.md
    docs/backward_analysis.md
    docs/agent_design.md
    docs/setup.md
- Each docs file must begin with:
    # [Title]
    > **Owner:** [team member]
    > **Last updated:** [date]
    > **Status:** Draft | In Progress | Final
- docs/architecture.md must include:
    - A Mermaid diagram showing module interaction and data flow
      (Cursor can generate Mermaid — use ```mermaid blocks)
    - The five integration contracts between team members
    - Which session state keys the Streamlit app relies on
- docs/data_pipeline.md must include:
    - The 11 cleaning steps in plain English (not code)
    - The train/test split rationale
    - Dataset quality findings (null rates, sparse channels, currencies)
- docs/optimization.md must include:
    - The objective function stated mathematically and in plain English
    - The four KKT conditions with a one-sentence plain-English explanation each
    - Why SLSQP is used instead of CVXPY (one paragraph)
    - Shadow price interpretation for a non-technical reader
- docs/backward_analysis.md must include:
    - All 7 stages described in plain English
    - What chart or output each stage produces
    - Why the user must confirm at Stage 7 before optimization runs
- docs/agent_design.md must include:
    - The agent's scope and what it refuses to answer
    - How guardrails work (input → sanitize → LLM → output check)
    - The three workflow phases and what the agent says in each
- docs/setup.md must include:
    - Step-by-step local setup from zero
    - How to get a Gemini API key
    - Environment variable reference table
- Update the relevant docs file whenever you implement or change
  the corresponding module. Docs lag is not acceptable for grading.
